Keeping to the shadows is easy. Once the door is closed there was
absolutely no light and the only sounds were from BATSCOUT where he
hovered in the air, his wings flapping somewhere in the darkness and
the sound of NIGHTSHIFT&#39;s own movement as he padded along.

There was the soft sounds coming from the movement lake above them.
The walls and ceiling seemed stout enough, but it was a reminder of
the hundreds of tons of water that was held suspended above their
heads as they moved. The air itself was cold, ice collecting in the
corners, but not enough to be a true hazard as long as one was
cautious.

Soon enough they arrived at the other side of the tunnel as they came
to the other door, the one that would allow them to enter CRYONOSIS
itself. Light blazed for a moment as BATSCOUT shined a light on the
door. It seemed to be a duplicate of the original door that was on the
other side of the tunnel.

It was closed.

